<br>
I don't have SoL yet (waiting to see if I get it for xmas), but from looking at the list, here's my choices for some of the best ones<br>
<br>
General:<br>
Natural Regen -    Think of it as permanantly having Phantom armor up.<br>
<br>
First Aid -  We can summon bandaids, might as well be good at using em<br>
<br>
Natural Int - more natual int = more flexible equip choice<br>
<br>
Natural resists (any type) - all good, but maybe better to have resist gear in bank and go with Natural int.<br>
<br>
<br>
Archtypical (casters):<br>
Mental Clarity -  mana regen, 'nuff said<br>
<br>
Spell Cast Subtlety - reduces hate, less us nuke more without pulling mob of Jaobober<br>
<br>
I like the one that reduces spell interruptions too, can't remember name of it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mage Class ones:<br>
To be honest I haven't thought through on these much yet, I welcome opnions.  I'm kinda partial to the one that lets us cast without malachite (nice for CR), but I doubt it's worth getting until you have points to burn.<br>
<br>
<br>
So, what do you all think?   Even if you're not planning on spending the time yourself to get them, I'll take any input on what looks useful, and what looks, um, &quot;typical&quot;...<br>
 <p>--
Chuck  (Prexus &lt;Dawn Breaker&gt; :: Fnordd / Sssuthaze / Tamuk / Fnobboz / Kault)
