Here's what I plan to spend my points on:<br>
<br>
General (6 points)<br>
3 to run speed (spent)<br>
3 to regen<br>
<br>
Archtype (12 points)<br>
1. Clarity <br>
2. Mastery<br>
3. Fury <br>
<br>
Class --<br>
<br>
Elemental form: water seems ok with 4/tic mana and EB.  Air is another decent choice, 30 sv all?  Fire and Earth seem pretty weak though.<br>
<br>
Elemental Pact (free pet): no way I'm spending 5 levels on this crap.<br>
<br>
Frenzied Burnout: at 6 points, its pretty spendy, but might be cool, we'll see.  I'd seriously consider this.<br>
<br>
Improved Reclaim Energy: ROFL please.<br>
<br>
Mass Group Buff: Oh golly.  9 points for this bitch, so we can cast our (1) group buff for FR dragons/boss mobs.  refresh time is 72 minutes for a buff that lasts 8 minutes.  thx useless<br>
<br>
Mend Companion: (1800 pet heal) lame<br>
<br>
Pet Discipline: (/pet hold command) 6 points WILL go to this, at some point.  Too bad we should get this by default at level 1 :P<br>
<br>
Quick Summoning: verrrry nice.  I would consider spending my first 18 Class points on this alone to get to level 3 = 50% faster casting pets/rods/etc.  Or maybe 9 points for lvl 2 (25%) then dump into Pet Discipline.<br>
<br>
